      "set:html": "<div class=\"sl-heading-wrapper level-h2\"><h2 id=\"interacting-with-session-data\">Interacting with session data</h2><a class=\"sl-anchor-link\" href=\"#interacting-with-session-data\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"sl-anchor-icon\"><svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"currentcolor\" d=\"m12.11 15.39-3.88 3.88a2.52 2.52 0 0 1-3.5 0 2.47 2.47 0 0 1 0-3.5l3.88-3.88a1 1 0 0 0-1.42-1.42l-3.88 3.89a4.48 4.48 0 0 0 6.33 6.33l3.89-3.88a1 1 0 1 0-1.42-1.42Zm8.58-12.08a4.49 4.49 0 0 0-6.33 0l-3.89 3.88a1 1 0 0 0 1.42 1.42l3.88-3.88a2.52 2.52 0 0 1 3.5 0 2.47 2.47 0 0 1 0 3.5l-3.88 3.88a1 1 0 1 0 1.42 1.42l3.88-3.89a4.49 4.49 0 0 0 0-6.33ZM8.83 15.17a1 1 0 0 0 1.1.22 1 1 0 0 0 .32-.22l4.92-4.92a1 1 0 0 0-1.42-1.42l-4.92 4.92a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.42Z\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sr-only\">Section titled ‚ÄúInteracting with session data‚Äù</span></a></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/en/reference/api-reference/#session\"><code dir=\"auto\">session</code> object</a> allows you to interact with the stored user state (e.g. adding items to a shopping cart) and the session ID (e.g. deleting the session ID cookie when logging out). The object is accessible as <code dir=\"auto\">Astro.session</code> in your Astro components and pages and as <code dir=\"auto\">context.session</code> object in API endpoints, middleware, and actions.</p>\n<p>The session is generated automatically when it is first used and can be regenerated at any time with <a href=\"/en/reference/api-reference/#regenerate\"><code dir=\"auto\">session.regenerate()</code></a> or destroyed with <a href=\"/en/reference/api-reference/#destroy\"><code dir=\"auto\">session.destroy()</code></a>.</p>\n<p>For many use cases, you will only need to use <a href=\"/en/reference/api-reference/#get\"><code dir=\"auto\">session.get()</code></a> and <a href=\"/en/reference/api-reference/#set\"><code dir=\"auto\">session.set()</code></a>.</p>\n"
